Date: 0/0/1989
Source: NZ English Newsletter
Author:
Vol / Page: 3/29
Edition:
Quote: <i>wool away:</i> The call of the shearer who wants the picker up to carry away a fleece. This has been done after each sheep, and fleeces are not left lying around on the floor while another sheep is being shorn.
Notes: (Wallace Shearing Glossary)

